# Multiplayer Board Game

This is a real-time multiplayer board game built using ReactJS for the client-side and Node.js with Socket.io for the server-side. The game involves a 5x5 grid where players can move pieces according to specific rules, with real-time updates between players.

A bonus task has also been implemented to add a new Hero3 piece which offers a new type of movement.

## Setup Instructions
```bash
# Clone the Repository
git clone https://github.com/Punnooze/HITWICKET.git

# move into the server folder
cd server 

# run the server
node server.js

# open a new terminal and move into the client folder
cd client

# run the client
npm run dev
```

## Features
- Real-time multiplayer gameplay with Socket.io
- Piece selection and movement validation
- Turn management and win condition checks
- Special piece handling and move history tracking
- Winning screen
- Game reset functionality

## Project Structure
- **Client**: The frontend of the game, built with ReactJS.
- **Server**: The backend, powered by Node.js and Socket.io for real-time communication.

## Prerequisites
- Node.js (v14 or above)
- npm (v6 or above)


# Playing the Game
- open the frontend on two separate browser windows and play the game. 



